The best one I can think is a couple weeks ago I did a monk epic for the millionth time. Since the mobs are pretty easy we decided to let the epic pet tank against Deep with the other 3 groups killed Vorash. We were really interested to see how the pet would do. Well pet got her down to 15 percent and only need 2 celestrial elixers.  This was before the extra pet hps were added so would be really interesting to see now.  <br>
I think the pet could tank any old world (old world including orginal and kunark) mobs fine, including many other epic type mobs like deep and vorash. <br>
<br>
While the epic pet melees very nicely and takes damage well. The thing that makes it really sick is the Damage Shield. Throwing a 50pt DS on anything is going to make it do vast amounts of damage.  <br>
<br>
I keep track of damage now and then and here is the average damage the epic pet takes against these mobs:<br>
<br>
Small Mushrooms in Fungus Grove -  83.34<br>
Toilers in Maiden Eye - 72.17 <br>
<br>
I am actually sure other classes take less then this per hit, but when you think about the fact that the DS is doing 60 percent damage back in the case of the small shrooms and 69.28 percent back to Toilers, you start to get some picture of why someone like Eldryc gets so frustrated. I also broke down damage on a couple of fights in Fungus Grove listed below:<br>
<br>
Mushroom(3) Damage inflicted on pet:<br>
<br>
Melee:<br>
Small Mushroom bashed 7 times for a total of 254 damage<br>
Small Mushroom hit 46 times for a total of 4,419 damage<br>
Small Mushroom kicked 5 times for a total of 161 damage<br>
<br>
Small Mushroom did a total of 4,834 points of damage<br>
<br>
Casting:<br>
Small Mushroom casted 34 times<br>
Small Mushroom was interupted 20 times<br>
Small Mushroom landed 2 clouds of noxious spores<br>
<br>
Epic Pet damage inflicted on mobs:<br>
<br>
Melee:<br>
Epic Pet bashed 20 times for 586 damage<br>
Epic Pet hit 194 times for 12,831 damage<br>
Epic Pet kicks 8 times for 230 damage<br>
Epic Pet Damage Shield hit for 2900 damage<br>
<br>
Epic Pet did a total of 16,547 points of damage<br>
<br>
Casting:<br>
Epic Pet casts stun 15 times<br>
Epic Pet landed stun 12 times (this inflicted anywhere from 0 - 1068 damage)<br>
Epic pet fist proc 41 times (this inflicted anywhere from 0 - 6560 damage)<br>
<br>
Mage Stats:<br>
Cast 58 level malise 3 times landing one on each of the small mushrooms<br>
Cast level 60 shock of the fiery blades 3 times for 2485 damage<br>
<br>
The Battles took a total of 6 minutes 33 seconds<br>
<br>
Just as a note, I really dont like posting info on boards like this but I thought it might be interesting for people to look at. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uelawnah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elawnah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cons Threateningly </span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#333333>(8/22/02 3:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/fguild75784frm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=104>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Elawnah/fullsize%5cdollies/elawnah3.gif height=151 width=99></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: verant's pet class (rant)</span><hr size=1> Now, just because I like to state randomness, even if I don't agree personally, allow me to throw this into the mix!<br>
